Aetna Inc. (new) : Roger N. Farah Joins Aetna Board of Directors



































0






06/28/2007 | 04:15pm CEST 


Send by mail :
Last Name :
Name :
From* :
To* :
(You can enter multiple email addresses separated by commas)
Message :
*Required fields






      Aetna (NYSE: AET) announced today that Roger N. Farah, President, Chief 
      Operating Officer and a Director of Polo Ralph Lauren Corporation, has 
      been appointed to Aetna's Board of Directors, 
      effective immediately. With the addition of Farah, 54, Aetna's 
      board increases to 12 members.
    

?We are very pleased to have Roger Farah join 
      our Board of Directors,? Aetna Chairman and 
      CEO Ronald A. Williams said. ?His strong 
      retail background gives him considerable expertise in consumer marketing 
      and segmentation as well as brand management. As the health care 
      industry model continues to evolve, it will be valuable to have diverse 
      perspectives and fresh thinking about how to best serve our customers 
      and members.?


      Farah has held his current positions with Polo Ralph Lauren Corporation 
      since April 2000. He has had a long and distinguished career in the 
      retailing industry, having served as chairman of Venator Group, Inc. 
      (now Foot Locker, Inc.) from December 1994 to April 2000, and as its 
      Chief Executive Officer from December 1994 to August 1999. He also has 
      held top executive positions with R.H. Macy & Co. Inc.; Federated 
      Merchandising Services, the central buying and product development arm 
      of Federated Department Stores, Inc.; Rich's/Goldsmith's 
      Department Stores; and Saks Fifth Avenue, Inc.
    

      Farah received a B.S. degree in economics from the University of 
      Pennsylvania in 1974.
    

      Aetna is one of the nation's leading 
      diversified health care benefits companies, serving approximately 34.9 
      million people with information and resources to help them make better 
      informed decisions about their health care. Aetna offers a broad range 
      of traditional and consumer-directed health insurance products and 
      related services, including medical, pharmacy, dental, behavioral 
      health, group life, long-term care and disability plans, and medical 
      management capabilities. Our customers include employer groups, 
      individuals, college students, part-time and hourly workers, health 
      plans and government-sponsored plans. www.aetna.com


      AetnaMedia Contact:Fred Laberge, 860-273-4788labergear@aetna.comorInvestor 
      Contact:David W. Entrekin, 860-273-7830entrekind@aetna.com
















 � Business Wire 2007





































